other_tests.procedure_name: Central venous catheter placement with guidance
other_tests.findings: Interval placement of a right-sided central venous line with the distal lead tip in the mid to distal SVC. No pneumothoraces. Right IJ line with the distal lead tip in the cavoatrial junction. Heart size is within normal limits. Atelectasis at the right lung base and low lung volumes due to poor inspiratory effort.
